"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391273","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-07","<p>Neither the Office for National Statistics nor other governmental statistical sources make such forecasts for steel. The Government forecasts can influence markets and therefore must be able to be robust.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-09-07T14:25:16.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391273/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391273/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391273/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-20","Iron and Steel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what forecasts the Government has made of steel (a) production and (b) demand in the next 20 years; and from which countries he expects the UK will import steel to meet that demand.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","8053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391274","Cabinet Office","false","2015-08-03","<p>All British, Irish, and qualifying Commonwealth citizens hold identical franchise rights therefore there is no marker on the electoral register to distinguish between electors who have registered as one of these nationalities.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2015-08-03T16:13:35.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391274/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391274/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391274/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-20","Electoral Register","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether Commonwealth voters are distinguished from British citizens on the electoral register; and if so, how.","false","Biography information for Lord Green of Deddington",,"Lord Green of Deddington","HL1639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391275","Department of Health","false","2015-07-23","<p>A Metropolitan Police (MPS) Freedom of Information revealed that they conveyed 931 patients to hospital in 2014. This makes up 0.1% of London Ambulance Service’s (LAS) case load in the same year. MPS and LAS continue to work together to develop protocols for dealing with the issue.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2015-07-23T11:06:19.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391275/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391275/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391275/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-20","Accident and Emergency Departments","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the answer by Lord Prior of Brampton on 16 July (HL Deb, col 686) regarding police ambulance support, what number of conveyances to Accident and Emergency departments 0.1 per cent represents.","false","Biography information for Lord Hughes of Woodside",,"Lord Hughes of Woodside","HL1640"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391276","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-10","<p>The amount of funding available to any student is affected by whether they have studied previously. Eligible students who return to England and enter higher education in the UK will therefore have any years of previous study taken into account when an assessment is made for a full-time tuition fee loan for a new course.</p><p> </p><p>One additional year of tuition fee loan may be available if the student was forced to withdraw from a previous course for compelling personal reasons. Students may ask that the conflict in their initial country of study be taken into account when they apply to Student Finance England for funding.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-09-10T14:29:01.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391276/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391276/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391276/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-20","Foreign Students: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will take steps to ensure that students studying abroad whose studies are interrupted by conflict have access to student finance on returning to the UK.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","8085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391277","Department of Health","false","2015-07-27","<p>NHS England has advised that the Cancer Drugs Fund (CDF) is reprioritised on a regular basis so that the resources available are used to the best benefit for patients.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As part of this, NHS England has taken the decision not to consider new drugs for inclusion in the national CDF list at this time and has made no decision on when new applications to the Fund will next be considered.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Clinicians will continue to be able to apply for cancer drugs not on the national CDF list through the Individual Cancer Drugs Funding Request procedure.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL1642 ; HL1644","2015-07-27T14:18:56.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391277/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391277/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391277/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-20","Cancer: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Prior of Brampton (HL777), why no assessment has been made of the impact of delisting from the Cancer Drugs Fund on the availability of cancer drugs in the United Kingdom.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391278","Cabinet Office","false","2015-09-07","<p>It will be for the independent FOI commission to determine the interpretation of its terms of reference.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","8036","2015-09-07T11:57:03.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391278/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391278/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391278/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-20","Freedom of Information: Commercial Secrets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Written Statement of 20 June 2015, HCWS153, on Freedom of Information, whether the terms of reference of the Commission on Freedom of Information will permit it to consider the appropriate scope of the commercial confidentiality exemption under section 43(2) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","8035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391279","Department of Health","false","2015-07-27","<p>NHS England has advised that the Cancer Drugs Fund (CDF) is reprioritised on a regular basis so that the resources available are used to the best benefit for patients.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As part of this, NHS England has taken the decision not to consider new drugs for inclusion in the national CDF list at this time and has made no decision on when new applications to the Fund will next be considered.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Clinicians will continue to be able to apply for cancer drugs not on the national CDF list through the Individual Cancer Drugs Funding Request procedure.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL1641 ; HL1644","2015-07-27T14:18:56.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391279/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391279/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391279/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-20","Cancer: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Prior of Brampton (HL776), what assessment they have made of the impact of the decision by NHS England to suspend the listing of new drugs on the Cancer Drugs Fund on patient access to new drugs being launched within the next six months.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1642"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391280","Cabinet Office","false","2015-09-07","<p>It will be for the independent FOI commission to determine the interpretation of its terms of reference.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","8035","2015-09-07T11:57:03.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391280/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391280/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391280/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-20","Freedom of Information: Commercial Secrets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Written Statement of 20 June 2015, HCWS153, on Freedom of Information, whether the Commission on Freedom of Information's terms of reference will permit it to consider the effective application of the provisions of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 to private companies that are providing under contract any service whose provision is the function of a public authority under section 5(1)(b) of that Act.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","8036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391281","Department of Health","false","2015-07-27","<p>This Government is committed to continuing to invest in the Fund. Proposals for evolving the Fund in a more sustainable way are under consideration. At its meeting on 23 July 2015 the NHS England Board agreed that these proposals will subject to public consultation later in 2015.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2015-07-27T14:04:41.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391281/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391281/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391281/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-20","Cancer: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether there are any plans to extend the Cancer Drugs Fund beyond April 2016; and whether there are plans to consult on further changes to the Cancer Drugs Fund’s Standard Operating Procedures in the event of the Cancer Drugs Fund being extended beyond April 2016.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391282","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-11","<p /> <p>This Government is committed to ensuring the Science, Technology, Engineering and Maths (STEM) workforce is diverse, reflects wider society and makes use of all the talents available to it, including those from low income backgrounds.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) funds and works with partners on a number of programmes which encourage a diverse range of people into STEM. BIS established a programme jointly run by the Royal Society and Royal Academy of Engineering aimed at understanding and addressing issues of diversity in the STEM workforce.</p><p> </p><p>As part of this programme the Royal Academy of Engineering’s Diversity Steering group recently launched their Engineering Engagement Programme. The programme aims to increase the number of people from low income backgrounds, women and black and minority ethnic backgrounds in engineering by changing the way employers recruit engineers.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-09-11T11:58:57.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391282/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391282/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391282/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-20","Engineering: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to increase the number of people employed in engineering from low income backgrounds; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","8008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391283","Department of Health","false","2015-07-27","<p>NHS England has advised that the Cancer Drugs Fund (CDF) is reprioritised on a regular basis so that the resources available are used to the best benefit for patients.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As part of this, NHS England has taken the decision not to consider new drugs for inclusion in the national CDF list at this time and has made no decision on when new applications to the Fund will next be considered.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Clinicians will continue to be able to apply for cancer drugs not on the national CDF list through the Individual Cancer Drugs Funding Request procedure.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL1641 ; HL1642","2015-07-27T14:18:56.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391283/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391283/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391283/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-20","Cancer: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when is the next opportunity that the Cancer Drugs Fund will accept new applications for review.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391284","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-10-01","<p>It is not possible to give an accurate estimate of the value of the Government Art Collection or individual works, neither of which have a current market valuation. The current monetary value of a work of art can be accurately assessed only at the time of purchase or sale or by professional valuation. In the former case, the Collection is not actively traded; in the latter, it would not be justifiable expenditure of public funds to have the whole Collection valued professionally.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-10-01T15:10:47.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391284/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391284/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391284/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-20","Government Art Collection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate he has made of the value of the Government Art Collection.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","7957"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391285","Department of Health","false","2015-07-27","<p>In my oral answer to the Noble Lord Hunt of Kings Heath on 13 July 2015, <em>Official Report</em>, column 345, I said that “the Government are committed to supporting NHS trusts to put in place sustained safe staffing by using their resources as effectively as possible for patients. The existing National Institute for Health and Care Excellence guidance on maternity settings and acute in-patient wards will continue to be used by NHS trusts. NHS England, working with NICE and other national organisations, will continue with this work in other areas of care and other healthcare professional groups”.</p><p> </p><p>Subsequently, the Secretary of State announced that the responsibility for safe staffing will be taken forward by Dr Mike Durkin as part of the decision to transfer the national functions for safety to NHS Improvement. Dr Durkin will work with the Chief Nursing Officer to complete the work started by NICE on safe staffing levels. This work will be reviewed independently by NICE, the Chief Inspector of hospitals, and Sir Robert Francis to ensure it meets the high standards of care the NHS aspires to.</p><p> </p><p>Future plans for safe staffing work will be developed in due course.</p><p> </p><p>Ministers and officials in the Department hold regular discussions with colleagues from Monitor, NHS England and NICE on a range of issues including safe staffing. We have no plans to publish details of these meetings or correspondence between these organisations on this issue.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL1646 ; HL1694 ; HL1695","2015-07-27T15:39:17.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391285/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391285/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391285/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-20","NHS: Staff","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to publish correspondence since 7 May between the Department of Health and (1) Monitor, (2) NHS England, and (3) the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence, regarding safe staffing levels; and whether they plan to publish the details of all meetings at the Department of Health at which safe staffing was discussed.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391286","Department of Health","false","2015-07-27","<p>In my oral answer to the Noble Lord Hunt of Kings Heath on 13 July 2015, <em>Official Report</em>, column 345, I said that “the Government are committed to supporting NHS trusts to put in place sustained safe staffing by using their resources as effectively as possible for patients. The existing National Institute for Health and Care Excellence guidance on maternity settings and acute in-patient wards will continue to be used by NHS trusts. NHS England, working with NICE and other national organisations, will continue with this work in other areas of care and other healthcare professional groups”.</p><p> </p><p>Subsequently, the Secretary of State announced that the responsibility for safe staffing will be taken forward by Dr Mike Durkin as part of the decision to transfer the national functions for safety to NHS Improvement. Dr Durkin will work with the Chief Nursing Officer to complete the work started by NICE on safe staffing levels. This work will be reviewed independently by NICE, the Chief Inspector of hospitals, and Sir Robert Francis to ensure it meets the high standards of care the NHS aspires to.</p><p> </p><p>Future plans for safe staffing work will be developed in due course.</p><p> </p><p>Ministers and officials in the Department hold regular discussions with colleagues from Monitor, NHS England and NICE on a range of issues including safe staffing. We have no plans to publish details of these meetings or correspondence between these organisations on this issue.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL1645 ; HL1694 ; HL1695","2015-07-27T15:39:17.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391286/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391286/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391286/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-20","Accident and Emergency Departments: Staff","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what the timetable is for the completion of the work by NHS England on safe staffing levels in accident and emergency care.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391287","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-29","<p>The Sousse terrorist attack has had a significant impact on tourist numbers in Tunisia: at the time of the attack there were an estimated 20,000 British tourists in Tunisia. This had dropped to around 2,000 before the Government changed its travel advice. Our travel advice has highlighted for some time the high threat from terrorism in Tunisia. Because of developments in the threat and intelligence picture since the attack, coupled with our assessment of the vulnerability of tourist sites, we took the decision to change our travel advice in order to ensure the safety of British nationals <br><br>Tourism usually accounts for around 15 per cent of Tunisia’s Gross Domestic Product. We and international partners are working with Tunisia to identify how we can best support their economy, including by increasing our bilateral and multilateral support. The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), and EU Foreign Ministers discussed economic support for Tunisia, including a significant increase in olive oil export quotas, at Monday’s EU Foreign Affairs Council. We also continue to encourage Tunisia to set out its plans for its economic development.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-29T16:18:10.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391287/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391287/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391287/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-20","Tunisia: British Nationals Abroad","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what estimate they have made, if any, of the impact of the Foreign and Commonwealth Office's revised travel advice for Tunisia on the Tunisian economy in terms of the loss of revenue from British tourism.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391288","Home Office","false","2015-07-30","<p>Around 700 people who are of concern to the Police and Security Services are thought to have travelled to the region since the start of the conflict. We estimate that around half of those have returned.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-07-30T13:41:57.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391288/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391288/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391288/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-20","Middle East: British Nationals Abroad","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many British nationals are estimated to have travelled abroad to Syria and Iraq to join extremist groups since October 2014; how many have since returned to the United Kingdom; and what is the total number of such people who remain in Syria.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391289","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-29","<p>The UK is part of a Global Coalition of over 60 countries and organisations who have come together to defeat the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL). The Coalition agreed that we will need to make concerted efforts on five lines: Military, Foreign Fighters, Finance, Stabilisation and Strategic Communications. The UK is playing a key role to support concerted efforts on these five lines. <br><br>The UK is a leading contributor to the military efforts to defeat ISIL. We are upgrading local forces – the Iraqi Security Forces (including Kurdish fighters) and the Syrian Moderate Opposition – through the provision of training and equipment and the RAF is part of the Coalition’s air support which is helping to defeat ISIL on the ground. <br><br>We are countering ISIL’s efforts to recruit foreign fighters by identifying recruitment networks, encouraging the exchange of information on travel routes, and ensuring Coalition members are sharing information to combat the flow of these fighters. <br><br>We have been working to prevent ISIL’s use of the international financial system and cutting off sources of funding, whether from oil smuggling, kidnap for ransom, foreign donations, or the trade in looted antiquities. <br> <br>The Coalition is committed to providing stabilisation support in Iraq. Essential services, civilian planning, local government and police will be needed in liberated areas to ensure relief and recovery, so that displaced people can choose to return to their homes safely. In the meantime, the UK is providing humanitarian assistance to the millions of people affected by ISIL’s brutality and chaos in Syria, Iraq and the region. The UK is one of the co-leads for the international working group on strategic communications. We are enabling credible voices across the region to speak out against ISIL’s atrocities and to encourage people not to support or promote ISIL. <br>We also support Iraqi Prime Minister Abadi and his efforts to lead an inclusive government and advance national reconciliation.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-29T16:17:40.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391289/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391289/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391289/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-20","Islamic State","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Prime Minister's commitment to work with the US to destroy IS, what their strategy is for doing so.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1649"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391290","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-07","<p>Self-employment makes a vital contribution to the economy, with over 4.5 million people currently self-employed, accounting for 14.5% of total employment.</p><p> </p><p>The government wants to raise productivity across all sectors and believes that self-employment can make an important contribution to achieving the objectives set out in Fixing the foundations.</p><p> </p><p>The government has asked Julie Deane OBE to carry out an independent review, reporting in early 2016, of the contribution the self-employed make to the UK economy and consider how they can be better supported.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-09-07T15:22:09.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391290/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391290/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391290/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential contribution of self-employed people to achieving the objectives set out in his Department's document, Fixing the Foundations: Creating a more prosperous nation, published in July 2015.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","7913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391291","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-27","<table><tbody><tr><td colspan="6" rowspan="5"><p>Five British pilots embedded with Coalition forces have been involved in combat missions over Syria under the operational command of their host nation. Ministers authorise the embedding of UK personnel on deployment with host forces. It has been long-standing practice not to announce such deployments.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>",,"Earl Howe",,"2015-07-27T14:19:48.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391291/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391291/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391291/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-20","Syria: Military Intervention","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many combat missions involving British pilots embedded with US forces have taken place over Syria since August 2013; whether Ministers gave permission for the involvement of British personnel in such missions; and if so, why Parliament was not informed.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391293","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-27","<p>As the Chancellor has said, we should not underestimate the impact that a Greek exit from the euro area would have on the European economy – or the knock-on effects on the UK. But the economic plan we have pursued in Britain these last five years has increased our resilience – and we will take whatever further steps are needed to protect the UK from new risks to our economic security. The Treasury continuously monitors global economic developments, including those in Greece, and their impact on the UK as part of the normal process of policy development.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The UK government stands ready to do whatever is necessary to protect and secure the British economy and financial system, and support businesses and individuals. As you would expect, these contingency plans take into account a wide range of scenarios.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2015-07-27T13:42:59.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391293/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391293/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391293/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Economic and Monetary Union: Greece","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the potential effect of a Greek exit from the euro on the United Kingdom economy; and what contingency plans have been made for that eventuality.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1651"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391294","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-09","<p>The July Budget document revealed that over 85,000 individuals had taken advantage of the new flexibilities for accessing pensions that were introduced in April 2015. Reliable data for Scotland is not available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC plans to publish statistics on take up of pensions flexibility in the Autumn</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-09-09T13:07:12.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391294/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391294/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391294/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Pensions: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people in Scotland have made use of the new pension flexibilities introduced on 6 April 2015.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","7915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391295","Department for International Development","false","2015-07-30","<p>There are an estimated 7.6 million internally displaced persons within Syria, and there are now over four million refugees from Syria in neighbouring countries. According to the UN, there have been over 278,000 Syrian asylum applications in Europe between April 2011 and May 2015.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-07-30T14:10:59.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391295/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391295/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391295/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-07-20","Syria","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their latest estimate of the number of Syrians displaced (1) within Syria, and (2) abroad.","false","Biography information for The Marquess of Lothian",,"The Marquess of Lothian","HL1652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391296","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-09","<p>The pension freedoms introduced on 6 April mean that the 320,000 individuals retiring each year with defined contribution pension savings are able to access them as they wish, and around 2 million people aged over 55 now have more options when they retire. Data for the proportion of people who have used the freedoms following a Pension Wise appointment is not collected.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As announced on 21 July, nearly 18,000 free Pension Wise guidance appointments over the phone and face to face are being delivered and more than 925,000 people have used the Pension Wise website, with many people returning to the site regularly.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","7917","2015-09-09T13:12:31.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391296/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391296/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391296/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Pensions: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people in Scotland have received guidance from the Pension Wise guidance service (a) face-to-face, (b) by telephone and (c) online.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","7916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391297","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-30","<p>All new HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) telephony advisers receive two days of call handling soft skills training, prior to handling customer calls. Further call handling training is provided depending on the needs of the advisor.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The first escalation for complaints from an adviser is to a Team Leader. 80 per cent of complaints are successfully handled at this point.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC’s Personal Tax Operations has a specific team who deal with customer complaints received via telephone.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC has a target of answering 80 per cent of all calls received.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information regarding the training and performance on telephony issues for other Government Departments is not held centrally and should be obtained from the Departments concerned.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley","HL1654","2015-07-30T13:33:52.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391297/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391297/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391297/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Government Departments: Telephone Services","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord O’Neill of Gatley on 9 July (HL898), what training in communication skills is provided for the officials in (1) HM Revenue and Customs, (2) the Home Office, (3) the Ministry of Justice, (4) the Department for Work and Pensions, and (5) the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills, who are responsible for helping members of the public who telephone with complaints or requests for information.","false","Biography information for Lord Quirk",,"Lord Quirk","HL1653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391298","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-30","<p>All new HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) telephony advisers receive two days of call handling soft skills training, prior to handling customer calls. Further call handling training is provided depending on the needs of the advisor.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The first escalation for complaints from an adviser is to a Team Leader. 80 per cent of complaints are successfully handled at this point.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC’s Personal Tax Operations has a specific team who deal with customer complaints received via telephone.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC has a target of answering 80 per cent of all calls received.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information regarding the training and performance on telephony issues for other Government Departments is not held centrally and should be obtained from the Departments concerned.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley","HL1653","2015-07-30T13:33:52.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391298/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391298/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391298/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Government Departments: Telephone Services","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord O’Neill of Gatley on 9 July (HL898), whether there are target times by which calls from members of the public are expected to receive attention when telephoning (1) HM Revenue and Customs, (2) the Home Office, (3) the Ministry of Justice, (4) the Department for Work and Pensions, and (5) the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills.","false","Biography information for Lord Quirk",,"Lord Quirk","HL1654"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391299","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-09","<p>The pension freedoms introduced on 6 April mean that the 320,000 individuals retiring each year with defined contribution pension savings are able to access them as they wish, and around 2 million people aged over 55 now have more options when they retire. Data for the proportion of people who have used the freedoms following a Pension Wise appointment is not collected.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As announced on 21 July, nearly 18,000 free Pension Wise guidance appointments over the phone and face to face are being delivered and more than 925,000 people have used the Pension Wise website, with many people returning to the site regularly.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","7916","2015-09-09T13:12:31.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391299/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391299/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391299/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Pensions: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people in Scotland who have made use of the pension flexibilities introduced on 6 April 2015 received guidance from the Pension Wise guidance service (a) by telephone, (b) face-to-face and (c) online.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","7917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391300","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-29","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) has held meetings throughout the past year with a number of diplomatic missions and international organisations about outstanding London Congestion Charge bills and fines, and other debts. The subject of a mission’s outstanding debts is also raised with all incoming Heads of Mission.</p><p>In March this year FCO officials wrote to all diplomatic missions with unpaid London Congestion Charges over £100,000 requesting payment of the outstanding fines as a matter of priority and to give them the opportunity to pay the outstanding fines, or to dispute them with Transport for London (TfL), before we published the details.</p><p>Statistics provided by TfL show that the vast majority (around two thirds) of diplomatic missions pay Congestion Charges. Diplomatic missions which do not pay, claim that the Congestion Charge is a form of tax from which they should be exempt under the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations (VCDR) 1961. The view of the Government is that there are no legal grounds to exempt diplomats and they are therefore expected to pay Congestion Charges. Officials from the FCO, the Department for Transport (DfT) and TfL continue work to identify a solution to the legal impasse with non-paying missions.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-29T16:16:39.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391300/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391300/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391300/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-20","Diplomatic Service: Tolls","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Statement by Baroness Anelay of St Johns (HLWS119), what action they have been taking on the issue of unpaid London Congestion Charge bills and fines incurred by diplomatic missions and international organisations, with what results, and when they expect a satisfactory agreement to be reached.","false","Biography information for Lord Quirk",,"Lord Quirk","HL1655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391301","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-11","<p>Updated Information on the impacts of Tax-Free Childcare on the labour and childcare markets will be published in due course.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","8179","2015-09-11T10:29:14.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391301/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391301/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391301/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will publish his Department's research on the effect of his policies on tax-free childcare on the labour market.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","7920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391302","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-29","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) has held meetings throughout the past year with a number of diplomatic missions and international organisations about outstanding parking fines and other debts. The subject of a mission’s outstanding debts is also raised with all incoming Heads of Mission. In April this year FCO officials wrote to all diplomatic missions with unpaid parking fines over £500 to give them the opportunity to either pay the outstanding fines, or to dispute them with the creditors, before the publication of the details to Parliament. Subsequent payments of parking fines, including amounts waived by councils, totalled £214,154.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-29T16:16:05.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391302/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391302/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391302/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-20","Diplomatic Service: Parking Offences","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Statement by Baroness Anelay of St Johns (HLWS116), what action they have been taking on the issue of unpaid parking fines incurred by diplomatic missions and international organisations to ensure fines are duly and regularly paid; and with what result.","false","Biography information for Lord Quirk",,"Lord Quirk","HL1656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391303","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-07","<p>At present the Government has no plans to introduce new taxes on food and drinks.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-09-07T15:04:20.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391303/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391303/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391303/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Food: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what his policy is on the taxation of high sugar and high salt food and drinks.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","7965"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391304","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-29","<p>The tragic losses of lives during the anti-Sikh riots of 1984 remain a source of deep pain to Sikhs everywhere around the world. We recognise the deep scars that this has left and the understandably strong feelings that exist to this day. We are aware of reports of the Indian Home Minister, Rajnath Singh, referring to the anti-Sikh riots as genocide. Any inquiry is a matter for the Indian government.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-29T16:15:41.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391304/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391304/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391304/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-20","India","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the statement in 2014 by the Indian Home Minister describing the 1984 killings of Sikhs in India as genocide, whether they are pushing, or plan to push, for an international inquiry.","false","Biography information for Lord Singh of Wimbledon",,"Lord Singh of Wimbledon","HL1657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391305","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-08-03","<p>The Government wants to move from a low wage, high tax, high welfare society to a higher wage, lower tax, lower welfare society. That means placing more emphasis on support to families on low incomes by reducing income tax through increases in the income tax personal allowance level and increasing wages, than on topping up low wages through tax credits.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The National Living Wage will not be linked to the rate recommended by the Living Wage Foundation. The Low Pay Commission has been asked to provide recommendations regarding the level of the National Living Wage in the future and an assessment of the pace of increase to reach the Government’s ambition of 60% of median earnings by 2020. In making its recommendations on the National Living Wage, the Low Pay Commission takes into account a wide range of evidence from across the economy.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-08-03T16:21:06.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391305/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391305/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391305/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-20","Living Wage","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to bring the National Living Wage in line with the rate recommended by the Living Wage Foundation by incorporating adjustments for cost of living and support received through tax credits.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of St Albans",,"The Lord Bishop of St Albans","HL1658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391306","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-07","<p>The Government is committed to making the UK the leading global FinTech hub, and has announced a large number of policy initiatives, including more supportive regulatory regimes for peer-to-peer, digital currencies, and other innovative firms.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government built on this record at the Summer Budget. First, Eileen Burbidge was appointed as the UK’s ‘Special Envoy for FinTech’, where she will represent UK interests in FinTech at home and around the world. Second, an international FinTech benchmarking exercise was announced to measure the UK’s performance and identify areas of best practice from around the world.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-09-07T15:35:18.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391306/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391306/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391306/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Financial Services: Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what support his Department is providing to promote the growth of the FinTech industry.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","7976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391307","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-08-03","<p>The UK has a national wage policy and we do not plan to introduce a regional wage policy. It is right that workers across the country should benefit from the new National Living Wage. The Low Pay Commission takes into account a wide range of evidence from across the economy in making its recommendations on the level at which rates should be set, and will continue to do so. This means there is a level playing field and that wage policy is simple for employers to understand and meet their responsibilities under the law.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-08-03T16:20:42.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391307/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391307/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391307/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-20","Living Wage: Greater London","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they are considering introducing a distinct London rate for the National Living Wage, following the principle established by the Living Wage Foundation for both a recommended national and London rate.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of St Albans",,"The Lord Bishop of St Albans","HL1659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391308","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-11","<p>The Office for National Statistics does not publish estimates of household debt by employment status.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-09-11T11:18:36.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391308/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391308/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391308/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent estimate he has made of levels of household debt in households where at least one adult is in work.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","8019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391309","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-08-03","<p>The overall maintenance support available to students in loans will increase to the highest level ever for students from low-income households. The Government will also continue to provide maintenance loans to students from all backgrounds to cover the costs of living while studying. These loans are only repaid once borrowers’ earnings rise above £21,000.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The priority for younger workers under 25 is to gain skills and experience and secure work - something that is already reflected in the National Minimum Wage rate structure where the youth rate is currently £1.40 lower than the adult rate. Wages tend to increase through the early 20s as workers gain more experience. Therefore, the wages of younger workers will continue to be underpinned by the core National Minimum Wage as recommended by the Low Pay Commission at the highest possible level without affecting employment.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-08-03T16:19:57.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391309/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391309/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391309/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-20","Personal Income: Young People","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to address income pressures on people aged under 25 in the light of the additional costs of student maintenance, reduced access to housing support and their ineligibility for the new National Living Wage.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of St Albans",,"The Lord Bishop of St Albans","HL1660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391310","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-09","<p>Treasury Ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery.</p><p> </p><p>Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-09-09T13:06:00.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391310/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391310/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391310/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Local Enterprise Partnerships: Leeds","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what meetings he has had with Leeds City Region Local Enterprise Partnership since the 2015 General Election; and what plans he has to meet with that organisation before 15 August 2015.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","8040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391311","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-29","<p>There is no justifiable link between Islamist extremism and British policy in the Middle East. As the Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), said on 20 July, “The root cause of the threat we face is the extremist ideology itself.”</p><p> </p><p>The UK continues to make a significant contribution to countering Islamist extremism and terrorism across the Middle East, including through the UK’s leading role in the Global Coalition to counter the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-29T16:15:22.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391311/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391311/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391311/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-20","Radicalism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of whether there is a link between Muslim extremism and United Kingdom policies in the Middle East.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL1661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391312","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-08","<p>At Summer Budget the Chancellor announced the opening of the bidding round for a new wave of Enterprise Zones across England. This round will focus on ensuring that all places in England can benefit from the programme, and the government encourages towns and districts to work with their respective Local Enterprise Partnerships to develop bids. The application process is now open and Local Enterprise Partnerships have until the 18<sup>th</sup> September to submit their bids.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-09-08T14:47:27.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391312/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391312/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391312/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Enterprise Zones","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraph 1.288 of the Summer Budget 2015, what process he plans for the establishment of new Enterprise Zones; and by when he plans to open the next bidding round for such zones.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","8043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391313","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-29","<p>The Government assesses that the EU plays a positive role in promoting conduct which is in line with Israel’s obligations as an occupying power under the Fourth Geneva Conventions of 1949.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-29T16:15:04.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391313/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391313/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391313/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-20","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the role of the EU in respect of Israel’s occupation of Palestinian territories.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL1662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391314","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-08","<p>At Summer Budget we announced the opening of the bidding round for a new wave of Enterprise Zones across England. This round will focus on ensuring that all places in England can benefit from the programme, and the government encourages towns and districts including Dewsbury to work with their respective Local Enterprise Partnerships to develop bids. The application process is now open and Local Enterprise Partnerships have until the 18<sup>th</sup> September to submit their bids.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-09-08T14:51:14.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391314/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391314/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391314/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Enterprise Zones: Dewsbury","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to his statement of 29 April 2015 to the Dewsbury Reporter, whether it is his policy to establish an Enterprise Zone for Dewsbury; and what targets he has set for the process of establishing such a zone to (a) commence and (b) be concluded.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","8044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391315","Department for International Development","false","2015-07-30","<p>The UK provided £349 million in support of Palestinian development between 2011-2015 and will provide a further £72 million in 2015/16. This includes support for both Gaza and the West Bank.</p><p>DFID's programme contributes to UK policy objectives of a negotiated two-state solution. Following the conflict in Gaza last year, the UK provided £17 million of immediate humanitarian assistance and pledged a further £20 million of early recovery assistance at the Gaza Reconstruction conference in Cairo.</p><p>We have already disbursed over 80% of the pledge. European Neighbourhood Instrument (ENI) is the main EU financial instrument for the OPTs which provides funding to support governance at local and national levels, private sector and economic development and water and land development. In 2014, EU funding through the European Neighbourhood Instrument (ENI) amounted €309.5 million.</p><p>The UK contributes to the EU Budget as a whole, and not to individual instruments within it. The UK’s share of the EU’s expenditure in EU instruments is approximately 14.5%.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-07-30T14:13:00.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391315/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391315/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391315/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-07-20","West Bank: Armed Conflict","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the cost to the public purse in the last five years of the conflict in the West Bank, both directly and via the EU.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL1663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391316","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-07","<p>At the Summer Budget the government announced that savings banks established under the Savings Bank (Scotland) Act 1819 will benefit from the same £25m carried-forward loss allowance for Corporation Tax as the building society sector. This will be backdated to 1 April 2015 and actioned through the Finance Bill 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Coalition Government took significant steps to support the credit union movement in Great Britain. These included increasing the maximum interest rate that credit unions can charge on loans from 2% to 3% per month; investing £38m in the sector through the Department of Work and Pensions’ Credit Union Expansion Project and launching a Call for Evidence which allowed all credit unions, regardless of size or influence, the opportunity to contribute their vision for the future of the sector to the wider debate. The Government is committed to continuing</p><p> </p><p>to support the credit union movement in making financial services more accessible.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-09-07T15:37:53.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391316/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391316/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391316/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Financial Institutions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what support the Government is providing to (a) mutual savings banks and (b) credit unions in (a) the UK, (b) Scotland and (c) Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill constituency.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","8051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391317","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-29","<p>The Government has regular discussions with European partners about Israel’s occupation of the West Bank. Our fundamental starting point in all our discussions is that Israeli conduct must be in line with International Humanitarian Law.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-29T16:14:53.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391317/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391317/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391317/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-20","Israel: West Bank","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with their European allies regarding any United Kingdom red lines for Israel in the West Bank.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL1664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391318","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-11","<p>No assessment has been made of the potential effect of proposed changes to tax credits and housing benefit in the Summer Budget 2015 on the number of abortions in the UK.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-09-11T10:37:18.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391318/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391318/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391318/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will conduct an assessment of the potential effect of proposed changes to tax credits and housing benefit in the Summer Budget 2015 on the number of abortions in the UK.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","8088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391319","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-29","<p>While officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv have not had any discussions with the Israeli authorities over these specific orders, we are pressing Israel to demonstrate accountability for its actions during Operation Protective Edge (OPE). Officials held discussions with the Israeli Military Advocate General’s office on 13 July and with the Israeli State Comptroller’s office on 15 July where OPE was raised.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-07-29T16:14:14.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391319/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391319/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391319/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-20","Gaza: Israel","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the government of Israel concerning the orders and directives given by Colonel Ofer Winter during Operation Protective Edge.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL1665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391320","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-07","<p>The Vehicle Excise Duty exemption for agricultural vehicles applies to vehicles used on public roads for journeys of up to 1.5 kilometres. The reforms to Vehicle Excise Duty announced at the Summer Budget will apply to cars first registered on or after 1 April 2017 and will not include any changes to the exemption for agricultural vehicles</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-09-07T15:12:11.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391320/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391320/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391320/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Motor Vehicles: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 20 June 2015 to Question 6981, whether agricultural vehicles used for journeys of more than 1.5 kilometres on public roads will be exempt from paying Vehicle Excise Duty.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","8082"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391321","Cabinet Office","false","2015-07-27","<p>There are three unpaid Ministers of State and three unpaid Parliamentary Under-Secretaries of State in the House of Lords. A full list of ministers by department is already in the public domain on the <a target="_blank" href="http://gov.uk/">gov.uk</a> website: <a target="_blank" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers">https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers</a>.</p>",,"Baroness Stowell of Beeston",,"2015-07-27T09:38:43.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391321/answer","Biography information for Baroness Stowell of Beeston","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391321/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391321/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-20","Ministers: Pay","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many (1) Ministers of State, and (2) Parliamentary Under-Secretaries of State, in the House of Lords are presently unpaid.","false","Biography information for Lord Trefgarne",,"Lord Trefgarne","HL1666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391322","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-07","<p>Distributional analysis of the impact of government policy across the household income distribution was published alongside the Summer Budget, and can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443229/PU1822_Distributional_Analysis.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443229/PU1822_Distributional_Analysis.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-09-07T15:23:05.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391322/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391322/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391322/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Personal Income","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will publish a distributional analysis of the effect of the measures announced in the Summer Budget 2015 on people in each income group decile.","false","Biography information for Mr Chris Leslie","Nottingham East","Chris Leslie","8089"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391323","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-30"," <p /> <p><strong> </strong></p><p>The recent IFS report is positive about the Government’s new approach to tackling the root causes of poverty: they said that “focusing on a broad range of inputs into life chances and causes of poverty is sensible.” They also add that “family worklessness certainly is a sensible thing to track if one wants to reduce the prevalence of low living standards.”</p><p> </p><p>This Government knows that work remains the best route out of poverty. Research shows that around three-quarters of poor children in families that move into full employment exit poverty. We are committed to supporting parents to move into work, increase their earnings, and keep more of what they earn. Universal Credit, our investment in childcare and the introduction of the National Living Wage will all play an important part.</p><p> </p><p>The Government also recognises that improving skills and progression is the key to making work pay. That is why under this Government we intend to create three million more apprenticeships over the next five years, and to help people move on to better jobs by improving qualifications and providing additional support through Jobcentre Plus.</p>",,"Baroness Altmann",,"2015-07-30T13:27:22.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391323/answer","Biography information for Baroness Altmann","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391323/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391323/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-20","Poverty: Children","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the report by the Institute of Fiscal Studies <i>Living Standards, Poverty and Inequality in the UK: 2015;</i> and how they plan to respond to the findings that nearly 63 per cent of British children living in poverty are in working families.","false","Biography information for Lord Tyler",,"Lord Tyler","HL1667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391324","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-07","<p>Distributional analysis of the impact of government policy across the household income distribution was published alongside the Summer Budget, and can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443229/PU1822_Distributional_Analysis.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443229/PU1822_Distributional_Analysis.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-09-07T15:25:07.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391324/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391324/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391324/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Personal Income","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will publish a distributional analysis of the effect of the Summer Budget 2015 for (a) 2015-16 and (b) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Mr Chris Leslie","Nottingham East","Chris Leslie","8090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391325","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-27","<p>No.</p><p> </p><p>We will return to Parliament for a separate decision if we propose to take military action against ISIL in Syria, but as the Prime Minister has said, if there were a critical British national interest at stake or if there were the need to act to prevent a humanitarian catastrophe, we would act immediately and explain to Parliament afterwards.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2015-07-27T14:59:16.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391325/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391325/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391325/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-20","Syria: Military Intervention","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the criteria that would allow air attacks on ISIL targets in Syria without prior reference to Parliament have been changed.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL1668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391326","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-09","<p>The Government will make an announcement on next steps in due course.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","8111 ; 8112 ; 8113","2015-09-09T12:57:06.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391326/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391326/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391326/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-20","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the terms of reference are for his Department's forthcoming review of debt administration.","false","Biography information for Sir George Howarth","Knowsley","Mr George Howarth","8110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391327","Wales Office","false","2015-07-29","<p>The Wales Office holds no record of the circular referred to.</p><p>When the National Assembly for Wales was established in 1999, all documents held by the Welsh Office at that point were transferred to the Assembly.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2015-07-29T09:38:09.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391327/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391327/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/391327/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2015-07-20","Sheep Dipping: Wales","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether, prior to September 1993, a circular was issued by the Welsh Office Poisons Unit indicating that doctors would not be presented with cases of sheep dip poisoning unless the patient could prove that they were employed in manufacturing such products or that there had been a spillage during transport; and if so, upon whose authority the circular was issued, upon what evidence it was based, and to whom it issued.","false","Biography information for The Countess of Mar",,"The Countess of Mar","HL1669"
